TITLE: Sen. Tim Kaine and hundreds of others have been stuck in traffic for more than a day due to D.C. winter storm
SUMMARY: Other stranded drivers in Virginia were forced to turn off their cars to conserve gasoline, even as temperatures fell well below freezing overnight.

TITLE: Biden disapproval hits new high as voters give him bad grades on economy, new CNBC/Change poll says
SUMMARY: Biden's disapproval rating reached a new high in December as more voters signaled their unhappiness with his handling of the economy.

TITLE: Joe Manchin says he has had no talks about resurrecting Biden's Build Back Better plan
SUMMARY: Majority Leader Chuck Schumer has insisted Democrats will work until they pass the Build Back Better Act, despite Sen. Joe Manchin's opposition to the bill.

TITLE: Criminal charge against former NY Gov. Andrew Cuomo is dropped
SUMMARY: Andrew Cuomo resigned as New York governor after nearly a dozen women claimed the Democrat sexually harassed them. So far, he has escaped criminal charges.

TITLE: January will make or break voting-rights push as Senate is set to consider rules changes
SUMMARY: The Senate will try to pass the Freedom to Vote Act and will consider filibuster rule changes if the voting-rights bill fails, Chuck Schumer said.

TITLE: Subpoenas issued to Donald Trump Jr., Ivanka Trump in New York attorney general probe of ex-president's company
SUMMARY: New York Attorney General Letitia James is investigating whether the Trump Organization misstated the value of real estate assets for financial benefit.

TITLE: Corporations, trade groups gave over $8 million to GOP election objectors following Jan. 6 riot, new study shows
SUMMARY: After the Jan. 6 riot, corporations and trade groups combined to give over $8 million to Republican lawmakers who objected to the 2020 presidential election.

TITLE: As prices soar, Biden aims to help independent meatpackers compete with industry giants
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden blames meatpacking industry giants for the soaring price of beef and chicken. So he's helping smaller meat processors compete with them.

TITLE: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot aims to avoid another Covid lockdown, but won't 'take that off the table' as omicron spreads
SUMMARY: Lightfoot's remarks came as Chicago starts requiring proof of Covid vaccination for most people to enter restaurants, bars, gyms and other indoor areas.

TITLE: Democrats look to salvage tattered legislative agenda as they face 2022 midterm elections
SUMMARY: President Biden's Build Back Better Act, government funding, Fed nominations, voting rights, and a research and development bill are all on Congress' to-do list.

TITLE: Biden to speak with Ukraine President Zelenskyy, says he 'made it clear' to Putin that Russia cannot invade
SUMMARY: Biden this week urged Russia's Vladimir Putin to lower the tensions with Ukraine, warning the U.S. was prepared to "respond decisively" if Russia invades.

TITLE: Friends in low places: These politicians' best pals are their worst enemies
SUMMARY: Rep. Matt Gaetz is only the latest example of a politician damaged by people they thought were their friends.

TITLE: Pro-Trump lawyer says his plantations were go-to spots for those aiming to overturn the 2020 election
SUMMARY: Trump ally Lin Wood told CNBC that his plantations in South Carolina were used as a hub for those who wanted to overturn the 2020 election.

TITLE: Warren Buffett tells Bernie Sanders he won't intervene in strike at Berkshire-owned company
SUMMARY: Bernie Sanders asked Warren Buffett to get involved in a strike at Special Metals, which is owned by Berkshire Hathaway subsidiary Precision Castparts.

TITLE: 'This is a crisis of the Kremlin's making': Biden and Putin speak as tensions mount over Ukraine
SUMMARY: The Biden-Putin call comes as Ukraine has warned for months that thousands of Russian troops were massing along its eastern border.

SUMMARY: The coronavirus pandemic has led to a new era of inflation inequality, economists warn, in which poor households bear the brunt of rising prices.

TITLE: Jury finds Jeffrey Epstein friend Ghislaine Maxwell guilty in sex crimes trial
SUMMARY: British socialite Ghislaine Maxwell was convicted Wednesday of luring teenage girls to be sexually abused by late sex criminal and financier Jeffrey Epstein.

SUMMARY: President Joe Biden and Russia's Vladimir Putin will speak as Russia continues a military buildup at its border with Ukraine.

TITLE: Biden advisor's brother plans to lobby for Taiwan company that developed Covid-19 vaccine
SUMMARY: Jeff Ricchetti was hired to lobby for biopharmaceutical firm Medigen, which has developed a Covid-19 vaccine.

SUMMARY: The Jan. 10 meeting will focus on arms control agreements, NATO and Russian military activity as well as rising tensions over Ukraine.

SUMMARY: Biden pledged to support governors struggling with Covid-19, but said the administration needs states to step up to solve the crisis.

TITLE: UK PM Boris Johnson to assess latest omicron data before deciding on new Covid curbs
SUMMARY: Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have already started new curbs to help stop the spread of the omicron variant.

TITLE: Philippine President Duterte's China pivot hasn't reduced tensions in the South China Sea
SUMMARY: China and its Southeast Asian neighbors including the Philippines have been embroiled in territorial disputes in the South China Sea for decades.

TITLE: Biden says he wishes he thought about ordering 500 million at-home Covid tests 2 months ago
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said that he wishes he had ordered 500 million free, at-home Covid tests two months ago.

SUMMARY: Trump claims documents sought by the Jan. 6 riot panel are protected by executive privilege, but President Biden had declined to invoke that privilege.

TITLE: Sen. Chris Coons, seven staffers who traveled with Defense deputy secretary have Covid
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris tested negative for Covid-19 as the omicron variant surges in the United States.

TITLE: New York will require masks and social distancing at scaled-back Times Square New Year's celebration
SUMMARY: Attendees at the Times Square New Year's Eve celebration will have to wear masks, New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio announced.

TITLE: U.S. bans imports from Chinaâ€™s Xinjiang region, citing human rights abuses
SUMMARY: Washington has previously warned businesses with supply chain and investment ties to China's Xinjiang province that they could face legal consequences.

TITLE: Supreme Court will hear challenge to Biden Covid vaccine mandates
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court agreed to hear legal challenges to the Biden administration's mandates mandating Covid-19 for millions of workers.

TITLE: House Jan. 6 probe seeks information from Rep. Jim Jordan about his contact with Trump
SUMMARY: The select committee wants to ask Republican Rep. Jim Jordan about his communications with then-President Donald Trump on Jan. 6.
